# Copy this file to .env (which is gitignored) and fill in the values below
# before running the backend for the first time.
#
# Why these are required:
# - compose.yaml has NO default values. Removing the fallbacks was deliberate:
#   it forces credentials to be a per-machine choice, never a value committed
#   to the repo.
# - Spring Boot reads .env via `spring.config.import=optional:file:.env[.properties]`
#   in application.properties, and `spring-boot-docker-compose` reuses the same
#   POSTGRES_* values to talk to the container it started.
#
# Sharing rules:
# - NEVER commit .env. NEVER paste your password in chat / issues / PRs / email.
# - To share a credential with the friend out-of-band: Signal, password manager,
#   or said verbally. Not GitHub anywhere.

# --- Local Postgres (compose.yaml + Spring's docker-compose autoconfig) ----
# Pick whatever values you like. The user/db names are arbitrary; only the
# password actually needs entropy. Generate one with:
#   openssl rand -base64 24
# or use your password manager.
POSTGRES_DB=spacegame
POSTGRES_USER=spacegame
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=<paste-a-generated-password-here>

# --- Future API keys (uncomment when needed) ------------------------------
# OPENAI_API_KEY=
